<p>It does make the article seem unpolished that both [EXPUNGED] and [REDACTED] are used for enjambment.</p>
<p>It seem to remember that the recent trend is to use data expunged in this fashion for information that's been corrupted and redacted for stuff that's been taken out intentionally. Of course, there is no canon.</p>
<p>I just find the use of the mid-word redaction / expungment to be kind of passe already. The frequency of use in this article only increases the feeling for me. The second redacted could easily be changed to the word 'details.' with nothing lost from the article, in my opinion.</p>
<p>The third redacted gives me the impression that you used it because it was safer than coming up with an estimate of how long the head would take to decay which might be questioned. Unless I'm missing the implication with the third redacted, it's kind of unnecessary.</p>
<p>Also, based on Enma Ai's comment about Psi-8, the only conclusion I can draw is that it didn't get out via grave-to-surface travel.</p>

